          "body": "Christ exploits each city's own resume. Sardis's two historical falls by night-assault while watchmen slept (Cyrus 549 BC, Antiochus 218 BC) inform the *wake up* command and the *thief-coming* warning (3:2-3). Philadelphia's location as a missionary outpost on the trade route to the east supplies the *open door* (3:8), and the city's repeated earthquake-displacement supplies the *pillar that will not go out* (3:12). Laodicea's three industries — banking-gold, black-wool textiles, eye salve — become Christ's three counter-offers: *buy from Me gold refined by fire, white garments, and eye salve* (3:18). Even the lukewarm metaphor (3:16) is hyper-local: the aqueducts brought Hierapolis's hot springs and Colossae's cold streams into Laodicea tepid and emetic. The civic boasts of each city become the parable Christ uses to diagnose it."
